text: Kremenets Mountains (; ) is hill range in Volhynia in western Ukraine, being the extension to east of Voronyaki.https://kremgory.in.ua/https://www.karpaty.info/ua/uk/te/kr/kremenets/sights/mountain/ They are the northern border of Podolia Upland. The average height is around 300-400 m (1200 ft). The highest point is Drabanykha (409 m/1342 ft).https://www.nationalparks.in.ua/pryrodni-parky/ternopil/kremenetski-hory/ ==References== Category:Volhynia Category:Mountains of Ukraine
title: Kremenets Mountains
